{
  "stem": "27509.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Radio was a, over there, a common-- a common means of communication.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And since Hitler came to power in 1933, the writing was on the wall.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody, of course, anticipated to what degrees, and where that tragedy will end, and how it will end.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But-- but everybody knew what was happening because it's the first acts of Hitler's regime was to take the-- the-- the people who were non-Germans Jewish citizen living in Germany and send them across the border into Poland.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The first thing we knew is that we had to set up on the Polish-- inside the Polish border-- camps to hold all those people who were evicted from Germany, not matter how long they lived there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was only the first-- the first act.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then came the Kristallnacht, with-- with-- with the burning of the synagogues and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then came the-- the economic boycotts of the Jews of Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then came the throwing out of the people from their positions and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was an unfolding picture, even for those who did not read You didn't have to go and read Hitler's to know what he really intended to do because you could read a book and say that he has written it.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But it doesn't mean that he was going to do it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But he was as good as his word.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The tragedy was that he was the worst at his word.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nothing, and it was not only that we as a family didn't [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- the objective situation of the Jewish people in Europe-- and I'm not talking only of Bialystok or Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The objective situation of the Jewish people of Europe was such that-- excuse me-- that realistically speaking, there was no plans to make.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
